781
00:30:43,528 --> 00:30:44,904
it'll lead you to a better place.

782
00:30:44,946 --> 00:30:46,447
That's a good way of thinking about it.

783
00:30:46,489 --> 00:30:47,656
It'll change you.

784
00:30:47,698 --> 00:30:49,095
Maybe it'll burn things away

785
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:50,820
from you that shouldn't be there.

786
00:30:50,909 --> 00:30:51,940
That's another thing.

787
00:30:51,965 --> 00:30:53,703
That happens, for example,

788
00:30:53,828 --> 00:30:55,640
if you are attracted to someone,

789
00:30:58,320 --> 00:31:01,975
you may do backflips to sort yourself out

790
00:31:02,085 --> 00:31:04,100
so that you're more attractive to them.

791
00:31:04,128 --> 00:31:06,560
Because if you're compelled by something and you

792
00:31:06,585 --> 00:31:08,575
want to be worthy of it, you'll let go

793
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:10,840
of the things that aren't worthy in you.

794
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,552
Let them burn away.

795
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:14,535
So that's part of the symbolism

796
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:15,600
of the burning bush.

797
00:31:15,805 --> 00:31:17,473
Anyways, he keeps investigating,

798
00:31:17,515 --> 00:31:20,160
and then the voice of God itself speaks to him

799
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:23,800
and reveals itself as the ground of being.

800
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:25,720
So what happens is, Moses

801
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:28,495
establishes a relationship with this thing

802
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:31,360
that compels him, that's so deep that he now

